      "id": "1495055028678037654",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-18T15:34:55.616+02:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "# Zone Priority - Zone by Zone Guide\n\n- **First Zone:**\n  - *First zone usually will make it so that basically the entirety of the map is safe from the storm, so the zone priority concept does not apply, as you will 100% still be at your drop.*\n\n- **Second Zone:**\n  - *Even if you do not pull 2nd zone, finish looting up your drop and play storm for a short period of time to maximize your loot, and focus on rotating to 3rd zone, as that is when zone priority really begins to apply.*\n\n- **Third Zone:**\n  - *At this point zone priority really starts. Your goal is to start moving towards center zone. If you are far, rotate early. If you are already in a good position, stabilize and avoid unnecessary fights. This zone is mainly about setting up your mid game (position, mats, info).*\n\n- **Fourth Zone:**\n  - *You want to already be well positioned before the zone closes. Focus on anticipating half-half and minimizing movement. If you have enough mats and don’t need a refresh, playing deadside is very strong. Otherwise, you should play the congested side to find refresh opportunities.*\n\n- **Fifth Zone:**\n  - *This is one of the most important zones of the game. You want to be fully set up before moving zones start (position, mats, heals). Try to stay as close to center as possible. Deadside is ideal if you are comfortable on resources. If you are low mats, you must look for refresh on congested side.*",
