    {
      "id": "1495055070054842480",
      "type": "Default",
      "timestamp": "2026-04-18T15:35:05.481+02:00",
      "timestampEdited": null,
      "callEndedTimestamp": null,
      "isPinned": false,
      "content": "- **Sixth Zone:**\n  - *First moving zone. Priority is to keep front side and not get held. Always try to move early with the zone and avoid getting stuck behind. Deadside is still strong if you don’t need refresh. If you are low mats, you need to look for refresh while rotating.*\n\n- **Seventh Zone:**\n  - *At this stage, you should aim to play on a high layer (2–3 layers below height). This gives you space, less pressure, and good awareness of height players. Ideally stay just below height so you are harder to see and less likely to be focused.*\n\n- **Eighth Zone:**\n  - *Look for opportunities to take height. If height is fighting, take advantage by moving front zone and applying pressure (spray). You can also take height using mobility or by applying pressure (spleef). If no opportunity, continue playing your layer with good positioning.*\n\n- **Ninth Zone:**\n  - *Final zones are about decision making. If you are mid/low ground, always keep front side and look for refresh. Try not to stay on the same layer as everyone else, create space whenever possible. If you see an opportunity to win the game (height or refresh), you must take it instantly.*\n\n- **Tenth Zone:**\n  - *From this point, all zones play out the same way. You must prioritize staying front zone at all times. Look constantly for refresh opportunities or chances to take height. Decision making and timing are key to winning.*\n\n- **Eleventh Zone:**\n  - *Same as zone 10. Stay front, secure refresh if needed, and look for height opportunities. Avoid getting stuck behind at all costs.*\n\n- **Twelfth Zone:**\n  - *Final moments of the game. Everything is about execution. Stay front, take any refresh opportunity you see, and if possible secure height to close out the game.*",
